  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. It's given that line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math> is parallel to line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane. This means that the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is equal to the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math>. Line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is defined by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 x minus 9 y equals 3\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. This equation can be written in slope-intercept form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals m x plus b\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi></math> represents the slope of the line and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> represents the <em>y</em>-coordinate of the <em>y</em>-intercept of the line. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 x\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></math> from both sides of the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 x minus 9 y equals 3\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"minus 9 y equals minus 4 x plus 3\"><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 9\"><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals four ninths x minus one third\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. Therefore, the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"four ninths\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math>. Since parallel lines have equal slopes, the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math> is also <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"four ninths\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect. This is the reciprocal of the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math>, not the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.&nbsp;</p>",
